communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Mutual Aid Agreements (Police)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Please provide any and all MOUs, contracts, or other written agreements with the City of Seattle related to the provision of police officers or other security assistance for the FIFA Club World Cup in 2025 and the World Cup in 2026.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse

communications.subject: Welcome to the Public Records Center!
communications.communication:
Dear Rose  Terse, 
Thank you for registering with the City of Kirkland Public Records Center. If you submitted the request yourself, congratulations you are done! If the City submitted the request on your behalf, please follow the steps below to log in to your account for the first time:  
  * Click the link to the Public Records Portal (http://www.kirklandwa.gov/depart/Finance_and_Administration/Public_Records/Public_Records_Request/PRRPortal.htm) 
  * Select "View My Public Records Request." 
  * Select "Edit Customer Account Information." 
  * Underneath the submit button, click, "if you don't know or have forgotten your password, click here." 
  * Type in your email address, and click send. 
  * Once you receive the temporary password and log in for the first time, the portal will ask that you change your temporary password. 
Now you can successfully monitor the progress of your request. Should you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact the City Clerk's Office at (425) 587-3190. 
 
City of Kirkland

communications.subject: Public Records Request :: P051041-041425
communications.communication:
Dear Rose  Terse, 
 
This will acknowledge receipt of your request for access to public records pursuant to the Washington State Public Records Act, Ch. 42.56 RCW. Your request was given the reference number P051041-041425 for tracking purposes. 
 
City staff has begun work on your request and will contact you within five business days, either with the records you have requested, to provide you with an estimate of what date the records will be available for you, or to request a clarification, if necessary.   Note that we may also direct you to the City’s website if the records are available there, notify you that some records may be withheld or redacted, or inform you that there are no responsive records. 
 
If you submitted your request to the Police Department, please call (425) 587-3481 if you have questions. If you submitted a request to any other department, please call the City Clerk’s office at (425) 587-3190. You can also monitor the progress of your request at the link below and you will receive an email when your request has been completed. 
 
Kirkland Public Records

Following a reasonable search, the City of Kirkland found no identifiable records responsive to your request. There have been no signed or executed contracts or agreements regarding these two events. 
Please note that the provisions of the Public Records Act, Ch. 42.56 RCW, pertain only to existing records and do not require the City to respond to requests for information or to create records that otherwise did not exist at the time the request was made. 
If you would like to submit a request with different parameters please feel free to do so. Should you have any questions, please do not hesitate to respond to this email through your portal account, or call the City Clerk's Office at (425) 587-3190. You have 30 days from the date of this letter to express concerns or ask questions regarding your request. It is the intent of staff to fully comply with chapter 42.56 RCW in a timely manner. 
The City now considers your request closed. 
Please note that by closing this request, the City does not intend to further address this request. The one-year period to appeal seeking judicial review has officially begun.
